gomodel:SYNGO_4674  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 2: Overexpression of EXO70 increases dendritic branching (infection at DIV0, analysis at DIV15, MAP staining)\nFig. 3: EXO70 shRNA rescues dendritic branching (infection at DIV0, analysis at DIV15, MAP staining): only 1 shRNA tested, no rescue with shRNA-resistant EXO70\nFig. 7: Overexpression increases, shRNA decreases number of Piccolo and Shank-positive synapses\nFig. 8: Overexpression increases, shRNA decreases SV recycling measured with FM4-64 dye\nFig. 9: Exo70 overexpression promotes spine maturation. Experimental description: M&M: Hippocampal cultures were prepared using a modified Banker's culture protocol. Briefly, hippocampi were dissected from embryonic Sprague-Dawley rats (E18)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4674" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
